  "prompt": "What is a good amount of money yearly to live more than comfortably in the USA?",
  "response": "The amount of money needed to live \"more than comfortably\" in the USA can vary significantly based on several factors, including location, lifestyle choices, family size, and financial obligations. However, here are some general considerations:\n\n1. **Cost of Living**: Major cities like New York City, San Francisco, and Los Angeles have high costs of living, requiring significantly more income compared to smaller towns or rural areas. In such cities, a household income of $100,000 or more may be necessary for a comfortable lifestyle.\n\n2. **General Guidelines**: \n   - In many suburban areas, an annual income of $75,000 to $100,000 can provide a comfortable lifestyle, allowing for housing, transportation, healthcare, and leisure activities.\n   - In lower-cost areas, this number could be lower, potentially around $50,000 to $75,000, depending on individual circumstances.\n\n3. **Family Size and Lifestyle**: A larger family will naturally require more income. Additionally, luxury expenditures like private schooling, frequent travel, and dining out can increase the amount needed to feel comfortable.\n\n4. **Savings and Investments**: A good quality of life often involves not just covering expenses but also saving for future needs, such as retirement, which might lead to a higher desired income.\n\nTo summarize, while an income of around $75,000 to $150,000 per year is often considered more than comfortable for many households across various parts of the USA, individual circumstances can greatly influence this amount.",
